  "prompt": "Why can't Barack Obama run for reelection as President in 2016?",
  "response": "Barack Obama could not run for reelection in 2016 because he had already served two full terms as President of the United States. The 22nd Amendment to the U.S. Constitution limits individuals to serving a maximum of two terms in the presidency. Obama was first elected in 2008 and then reelected in 2012, completing his second term in January 2017. Therefore, he was ineligible to run for president again in 2016.",
